Now that the ffmpeg skill is loaded, let's analyze the current situation and plan the next steps.

Analysis:
The ffmpeg skill is loaded, and we have the prerequisites and methods for keyframe extraction. We need to extract keyframes from the video file `/root/super-mario.mp4` and store them in the `/root` folder.

Plan:
We will use Method 1: Select Filter (More Control) to extract keyframes. We will specify the input video file, output pattern, and other options as required.

Commands:

```json
{
  "analysis": "Loaded ffmpeg skill and analyzed the current situation. We need to extract keyframes from the video file /root/super-mario.mp4 and store them in the /root folder.",
  "plan": "Use Method 1: Select Filter (More Control) to extract keyframes. Specify the input video file, output pattern, and other options as required.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ffmpeg -i /root/super-mario.mp4 -vf \"select='eq(pict_type,I)'"\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "keyframe_%03d.png\"\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "-vsync vfr\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cd /root\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir keyframes\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ffmpeg -i /root/super-mario.mp4 -vf \"select='eq(pict_type,I)'"\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "keyframes/keyframe_%03d.png\"\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "-vsync vfr\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": false
}
```

Note: I've broken the long ffmpeg command into multiple lines for readability. The actual keystrokes should be sent as a single line.
